Subject: [PATCH v6 06/10] arm64: snapshot thread flags
Date:   Fri, 22 Oct 2021 14:56:39 +0100
Message-Id: <20211022135643.7442-7-mark.rutland@arm.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.11.0
In-Reply-To: <20211022135643.7442-1-mark.rutland@arm.com>
References: <20211022135643.7442-1-mark.rutland@arm.com>
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org

Some thread flags can be set remotely, and so even when IRQs are
disabled, the flags can change under our feet. Generally this is
unlikely to cause a problem in practice, but it is somewhat unsound, and
KCSAN will legitimately warn that there is a data race.

To avoid such issues, a snapshot of the flags has to be taken prior to
using them. Some places already use READ_ONCE() for that, others do not.

Convert them all to the new flag accessor helpers.

Signed-off-by: Mark Rutland <mark.rutland@arm.com>
Acked-by: Will Deacon <will@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Paul E. McKenney <paulmck@kernel.org>
Cc: Catalin Marinas <catalin.marinas@arm.com>
